<body>
    <h1>Binary files handling</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>The eZ Publish 5 API supports multiple binary file handling mech=
anisms by means of an&nbsp;<code>IOHandler</code>&nbsp;interface. This feat=
ure is used by the <a href=3D"/display/EZP/The+BinaryFile+FieldType">Binary=
File</a>, <a href=3D"/display/EZP/The+Media+FieldType">Media</a> and <a hre=
f=3D"/display/EZP/The+Image+FieldType">Image</a> FieldTypes.</p>
<p>Starting from versions 5.4 / 2014.09, a native IO handler is available.<=
/p>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-inf=
ormation">
<span class=3D"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-informa=
tion-macro-icon"></span>
<div class=3D"confluence-information-macro-body">
The LegacyKernel IO handler, that runs legacy kernel callbacks, is removed.
</div>
</div>
<h1 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-NativeIOhandlerYellow5.4/2014.09">Native IO h=
andler <span class=3D"status-macro aui-lozenge aui-lozenge-current">5.4 / 2=
014.09</span></h1>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The unique <code>IOHandler</code> interface is removed, replace by two d=
istinct interfaces:</p>
<ul class=3D"task-list">
<li><code>eZ\Publish\IO\IOMetadataHandler</code>: Stores &amp; reads metada=
ta (validity, size...)</li>
<li><code>eZ\Publish\IO\IOBinarydataHandler</code>: Stores &amp; reads bina=
rydata (actual contents)</li>
</ul>
<p>The IOService uses both.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-Configuration"><a class=3D"external-link" hre=
f=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_spec/doc/=
specifications/io/native_io_handlers.md#configuration" name=3D"user-content=
-configuration" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>Configuration</h2>
<p>IO handling can now be configured using semantic configuration.</p>
<p>Which IO handlers (metadata &amp; binarydata) is configurable by siteacc=
ess. This is the default configuration:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ezpublish:
    system:
        default:
            io:
                metadata_handler: default
                binarydata_handler: default
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p><br><code> </code></p>
<p>metadata and binarydata handlers are configured in the <code>ez_io</code=
> extension. This is what the configuration looks like for the default hand=
lers. It declares a metadata handler and a binarydata handler, both labelle=
d 'default'. Both handlers are of type 'flysystem', and use the same flysys=
tem adapter, labelled 'default' as well.</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">ez_io:
    metadata_handlers:
        default:
            flysystem:
                adapter: default
    binarydata_handlers:
        default:
            flysystem:
                adapter: default
</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>The 'default' flysystem adapter's directory is based on your site settin=
gs, and will automatically be set to <code>%ezpublish_legacy.root_dir%/$var=
_dir$/$storage_dir$</code> (example: <code>/path/to/ezpublish_legacy/var/ez=
demo_site/storage</code>).</p>
<h2 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-ThenativeFlysystemhandler."><a class=3D"exter=
nal-link" href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native=
_io_spec/doc/specifications/io/native_io_handlers.md#the-native-flysystem-h=
andler" name=3D"user-content-the-native-flysystem-handler" rel=3D"nofollow"=
></a>The native Flysystem handler.</h2>
<p><a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_=
spec/doc/specifications/io/flysystem.thephpleague.com" class=3D"external-li=
nk" rel=3D"nofollow">league/flysystem</a> (along with <a href=3D"https://gi=
thub.com/1up-lab/OneupFlysystemBundle/" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofo=
llow">FlysystemBundle</a>) is an abstract file handling library.</p>
<p>It is used as the default way to read &amp; write content binary files i=
n eZ Publish. It can use the local filesystem (our default configuration), =
but is also able to read/write to sftp, zip or cloud filesystems (dropbox, =
rackspace, aws-s3).</p>
<h3 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-handleroptions"><a class=3D"external-link" hr=
ef=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_spec/doc=
/specifications/io/native_io_handlers.md#handler-options" name=3D"user-cont=
ent-handler-options" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>handler options</h3>
<h4 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-adapter"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D"h=
ttps://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_spec/doc/specif=
ications/io/native_io_handlers.md#adapter" name=3D"user-content-adapter" re=
l=3D"nofollow"></a>adapter</h4>
<p>The adapter is the 'driver' used by flysystem to read/write files. Adapt=
ers can be declared using <code>oneup_flysystem</code> as follows:</p>
<div class=3D"code panel pdl" style=3D"border-width: 1px;">
<div class=3D"codeContent panelContent pdl">=20
<pre class=3D"brush: php; gutter: false; theme: Eclipse" style=3D"font-size=
:12px;">oneup_flysystem:
    adapters:
        default:
            local:
                directory: "/path/to/directory"</pre>=20
</div>
</div>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p>How to configure other adapters can be found on the <a href=3D"https://g=
ithub.com/1up-lab/OneupFlysystemBundle/blob/master/Resources/doc/index.md#s=
tep3-configure-your-filesystems" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">b=
undle's online documentation</a>. Note that we do not use the Filesystems c=
onfiguration described in this documentation, only the adapters.</p>
<h2 id=3D"Binaryfileshandling-Upgrading"><a class=3D"external-link" href=3D=
"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/blob/native_io_spec/doc/spec=
ifications/io/native_io_handlers.md#upgrading" name=3D"user-content-upgradi=
ng" rel=3D"nofollow"></a>Upgrading</h2>
<p>For those using the default <code>eZFSFileHandler</code>, no configurati=
on should be required, and things should just work like before, but without=
 legacy kernel callbacks for manipulating images &amp; binary files.</p>
<p>For those using the DFS cluster file handler, a new native handler is av=
ailable. See the <a href=3D"https://github.com/ezsystems/ezpublish-kernel/b=
lob/master/doc/specifications/io/legacy_dfs_cluster.md" class=3D"external-l=
ink" rel=3D"nofollow">DFS specification</a>.</p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
